cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.BE, cs.NE, cs.HC

The paper deals with the problem of heart rate estimation from PPG signals affected by motion artifacts. This involves signal processing, modeling, and estimation, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of an accelerometer to reduce motion artifacts also involves biomechanical engineering (cs.BE). The proposed method involves modeling the signals using harmonic sums, which is a technique used in signal processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with wearable technology and health monitoring, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
